{
  "texts": [
    "For arguments about the place of consciousness in human and other life see, for example, Chalmers 1996 and Reber 2018.",
    "It is interesting that basic moral categories can be safely assumed to be common to many societies.",
    "This is not to say that some human socialisation does not take the form of correcting ethical and other kinds of mistake and misjudgement: humans too are always learning from wiser or more experienced persons, but they already have the basic building blocks of truth and consistency to support these corrections.",
    "See Collins 2020 'Interactional Imogen' for a discussion of the relationship of the human brain to linguistic competence for the role of 'interactional expertise' -which is language fluency acquired by socialisation, in human societies.",
    "SeeCollins et al 2022a, b, notably Fig. 12.2."
  ]
}